{"body":"The new per-slot `slot_suspended` issue id adds the slot number, but the config-entry unload cleanup still deletes only `slot_suspended_{entry_id}_{lock_entity_id}` in `custom_components/lock_code_manager/__init__.py:671-673`. Any per-slot suspended repair issue created here will therefore be orphaned when the entry unloads. Update the unload cleanup to iterate the configured slots for each lock a","line":441,"path":"custom_components/lock_code_manager/sync.py"}
{"body":"This docstring says the windowed breaker latches until `reset()`, but `tripped` returns false once `now - _first_failure \u003e window` and the new tests assert that behavior. Please update the class documentation so callers do not rely on a latch that the implementation does not provide.\n","line":26,"path":"custom_components/lock_code_manager/resilience.py"}
{"body":"This reason says syncing resumes when the lock recovers, but this branch is for a slot-level non-convergence suspension and does not mark the lock unreachable. The slot can be retried on a later sync check while the lock is already reachable, so the repair reason should describe the slot-level retry/recovery condition instead of lock recovery.\n","line":631,"path":"custom_components/lock_code_manager/sync.py"}
{"body":"The repair description says syncing for this slot resumes when the lock recovers, but slot-level suspensions created by the new breaker do not necessarily make the lock unreachable. Please adjust the user-facing text to describe the actual slot-level recovery/retry behavior rather than lock recovery.\n","line":207,"path":"custom_components/lock_code_manager/strings.json"}
{"body":"The repair description says syncing for this slot resumes when the lock recovers, but slot-level suspensions created by the new breaker do not necessarily make the lock unreachable. Please keep this translation in sync with the corrected source string so users are not told to wait for a lock recovery that may never occur.\n","line":207,"path":"custom_components/lock_code_manager/translations/en.json"}

